About the Series:
The series is primarily set in Yorkshire, and follows the work of two detectives that are 
thrown together as partners.
Episodes in this series are divided on on the DVDs into part 1 and part 2 but I have encoded
these together to give the original episode as broadcast, so don't be supprised at credits
at 45 minutes in, as the whole episode is there and all episodes are approx 90 minutes. 

Episode 1 "A Game of Soldiers"
Dalziel and Pascoe investigate the murder of American tourist Nancy D'Amato, whose body 
is found by squaddies out on a training exercise.

Episode 2 "The Price of Fame"
Pascoe and Milligan are forced to investigate the suspicious death of a holiday village 
entertainer after Dalziel is suspended for his conduct during an interview with 
a kidnapping suspect.

Episode 3 "Great Escapes"
On a stormy night out on the Yorkshire moors, Dalziel's car breaks down on the way back 
from a charity do, leaving him stranded for the evening.

Episode 4 "Soft Touch"
The autopsy of a Russian national who is found dead face down in a lake reveals that 
someone tried to murder him two years previously with an AK-47 bullet which became 
lodged in his spine.
